In Ukraine, they offered to send Russians to prison for illegal crossing the border.
The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine has registered a draft law under which Russians may be criminally punished in the Republic for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, a document registered in the Ukrainian Parliament ' s electronic database provides for three years ' imprisonment for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained at the border with the weapon, the time of detention would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians who had tried to enter Russia outside the designated entry points.
